s://github.com/vicdeo","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vicdeo/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vicdeo/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vicdeo/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vicdeo/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vicdeo/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vicdeo/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vicdeo/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vicdeo/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vicdeo/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2012-12-13t21:35:17z","updated_at":"2012-12-13t21:39:00z","body":"@deepdiver1975 it's not mdb2-related, it's installation flow. \r\nwhen mysql 'root' account is used and the name for owncloud admin is set to 'dummy'. owncloud creates db user oc_dummy and grants permissions on newly created database to this user. \r\n\r\nif db user oc_dummy exists prior to oc installation wrong credentials are used by owncloud and installation fails.\r\n\r\nmost easiest way to reproduce:\r\n1. install 1st owncloud instance with mysql using privileged (root)  mysql user. set owncloud admin name to 'admin'. other settings are not essential\r\n2. repeat step 1. installation fails.\r\n\r\nreproducible both with master and stable45"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/13629436","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/108#issuecomment-13629436","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/108","id":13629436,"user":{"login":"vicdeo","id":991300,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/57b8c1e26d502d5414e4b2fb875d2994?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2fe8357fefe8bad5436de368fa5a419461.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"57b8c1e26d502d5414e4b2fb875d2994","url":"https://api.github.com/users/vicdeo","html_url":"https://github.com/vicdeo","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vicdeo/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vicdeo/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vicdeo/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vicdeo/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vicdeo/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vicdeo/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vicdeo/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vicdeo/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vicdeo/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-02-15t21:37:18z","updated_at":"2013-02-15t21:37:57z","body":"it's fixed in master with #1148 , there is a warning now:\r\n>mysql user 'oc_admin'@'localhost' exists already.\r\n>drop this user from mysql\r\n\r\nthus it's still not possible to install 2 owncloud instances using privileged mysql account using  the same username for owncloud admin account. \r\n\r\nnot backported to stable45.\r\n@deepdiver1975 can we close this issue?"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/13630904","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/108#issuecomment-13630904","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/108","id":13630904,"user":{"login":"tanghus","id":533222,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/e625b634822713b2e346ff7c67d26775?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f6d9c90af1c12f5a88e4d5f216bbc1979.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"e625b634822713b2e346ff7c67d26775","url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus","html_url":"https://github.com/tanghus","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/subscripti